709
01:28:13,935 --> 01:28:16,552
How were we supposed to know?

710
01:28:18,648 --> 01:28:20,264
Yeah!

711
01:28:20,483 --> 01:28:21,974
Right.

712
01:28:22,902 --> 01:28:25,986
How were you supposed to know?

713
01:28:26,197 --> 01:28:29,781
Fucking men like you built the hydrogen bomb.

714
01:28:29,993 --> 01:28:34,203
Men like you thought it up.

715
01:28:38,001 --> 01:28:41,039
You think you're so creative.

716
01:28:41,254 --> 01:28:44,292
You don't know what it's like
to really create something,

717
01:28:44,507 --> 01:28:48,091
to create a life,
to feel it growing inside you.

718
01:28:48,303 --> 01:28:50,545
All you know how to create
is death and destruction.

719
01:28:50,763 --> 01:28:52,129
Mom!

720
01:28:53,099 --> 01:28:56,718
We need to be a little more
constructive here. Okay?

721
01:28:56,936 --> 01:28:58,893
We still have to stop this
from happening, don't we?

722
01:28:59,105 --> 01:29:00,812
But I thought...

723
01:29:02,025 --> 01:29:05,860
Aren't we changing things right now,
changing the way it goes?

724
01:29:06,070 --> 01:29:09,609
That's right. There's no way
I'm gonna finish the new processor.

725
01:29:09,824 --> 01:29:12,487
Not now. Forget it. I'm out of it.

726
01:29:12,702 --> 01:29:16,286
- I'll quit Cyberdyne tomorrow.
- That's not good enough.

727
01:29:16,497 --> 01:29:19,490
- No one must follow your work.
- Right.

728
01:29:20,585 --> 01:29:24,420
All right, then we have to destroy
all the stuff at the lab:

729
01:29:24,630 --> 01:29:29,045
the files, the disk drives,
everything, everything here.

730
01:29:29,886 --> 01:29:32,720
Everything. I don't care.

731
01:29:34,724 --> 01:29:35,510
The chip.

732
01:29:36,142 --> 01:29:37,678
- Do you know about the chip?
- What chip?

733
01:29:37,894 --> 01:29:39,385
They keep it in a vault at Cyberdyne.

734
01:29:39,604 --> 01:29:40,845
It must be from the other one like you.

735
01:29:41,064 --> 01:29:45,434
- The CPU from the first Terminator.
- Son of a bitch! I knew it!

736
01:29:45,651 --> 01:29:48,234
